; Regression test for issue #860: %D used in date_format command returns entire date (BZ#860)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/860
; %D in strftime means the full date as MM/DD/YY (equivalent to %m/%d/%y)
; When used with --date-format (or -y), ledger should format dates using strftime semantics

2024/01/15 Test Payee
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

test reg -y '%D'
01/15/24 Test Payee            Expenses:Food                 $10.00       $10.00
                               Assets:Cash                  $-10.00            0
end test
